up to an arresting and thought-provoking picture of the state of world literature today.Key FeaturesA powerful statement of the significance of literature in the modern world, and a call-to-arms for those who believe that fine writing is endangeredContributors include well-known contemporary novelists such as: China Mieville, Ahdaf Soueif, Kapka Kassabova, Irvine Welsh, Ali Smith and Kirsty GunnProvides an international perspective on the issues facing writers and writing in general, and the present-day novel in particularA new and valuable resource for academics and students, and a fascinating primer for a wider readership – for those who want to know how fiction functions & who like to get an insight into the thought processes of creative artists  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aA New Age Of Fiction,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAl-Barghouti, Tamim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarley, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBehrendt, Larissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBris, Michel Le, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurgess, Melvin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButler, Cortina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCole, Teju, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooke, Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDongala, Emmanuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEr, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGray, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https